						<summary>

						<p>Registers a grant of house-sites for the <hi rend="italic">bhaṭṭas</hi> and for the deity apparently Vēdanārāyaṇa-perumāḷ, free of taxes in the <hi rend="italic">agaram</hi> (name not given) formed in the king's name in Tirunārāyaṇapuram. The record is engraved below No. 220 and is damaged. The king probably is Sundara Pāṇḍya, brother of Jaṭāvarmaṉ Vīra-Pāṇḍya (Vide Nos. 219 and 220 below).</p>						

						</summary>
